Chess random move simulator
Intended as practice, does not use best algorithms at all, mostly random
Options:

Input a board (text)
Return a random (but legal) move.
Enter a move, have the program return one -- playing against a random computer
basically.
Return a list of pieces in immediate danger
Query whether a piece is in immediate danger
Query which pieces can take a particular board square
Return list of legal moves for a piece
Output option: Board with pieces marked (2D)
	Or plain text
Write in C++

Example board:

// black - lowercase, white - uppercase
// replace with UTF-8 pieces if font is available

8   h d m g k m d h
7   n n n n n n n n
6   . . . . . . . . 
5   . . . . . . . . 
4   . . . . . . . . 
3   . . . . . . . . 
2   N N N N N N N N
1   H D M G K M D H

    a b c d e f g h 
